# 6. 目指したい場所

Ena: ...
Ena: (We're doing stills of fruit today... I should be fine since I've practiced drawing them at home.)
Ena: (I was so bad when I first started coming here...)
Ena: (My perspective was all messed up, my lines were all crooked... I knew what I was going to be told.)
Ena: (Compared to then, I feeling like I'm doing a lot better now.)
Ena: (But it's not enough.)
Ena: (All I've done so far is sort of make up for lost time. The others are still miles ahead of me.)
Ena: I just need to keep drawing...
Ena: (One piece at a time without cutting any corners. I need to keep finding ways to get better.)
Len: <Is this her art class...?>
Rin: <Looks like it.>
Rin: <I came to take a look the other day when she was having trouble with what she was drawing...>
Rin: <They all look really serious...>
Len: <Y-Yeah, it's kinda scary...>
Len: <Ena...>
Rin: <Thank goodness...>
Len: <Huh?>
Rin: <She always looked like she was in pain whenever she was drawing anything...>
Rin: <But things seem different today.>
Ena: *Sigh*
Ena: (He bit my head off again today... To be fair, that's a pretty normal occurrence now.)
Ena: (But I feel like he's been making comments about the finer details lately...)
Ena: (Not too long ago, he'd usually just say that I need to draw everything again from scratch...)
Rin: <Ena...>
???: Ena!
Ena: Huh...?
Futaba: Nice work today! Are you free after this?
Futaba: I was hoping that on the way home, we could go to this really yummy cheesecake shop that I found.
Ena: Huh? Cheesecake...?
Ena: Hmm... I'm gonna have to say yes to that.
Futaba: Really?! Then, let's go!
Len: <Is she Ena's friend...?>
Rin: <I think so. Let's stick around to see what happens.>
Ena: Mmm! This cheesecake's amazing...!
Ena: These fruits make it look gorgeous, and the cheese is so rich too. My mouth is in heaven right now...
Ena: Thanks for bringing me here, Futaba!
Futaba: No, I've been meaning to invite you for a little while now. I'm so glad that you could come today!
Ena: You're that glad? Well, it does make me happy to hear that...
Ena: Still, this reminds me of how we used to come to places like this.
Futaba: Yeah! Class always seems to end just in time when you start feeling hungry for some reason.
Futaba: Mr. Yukihira's a harsh critic... But I was always able to keeping returning because I was excited to go somewhere with you after class.
Ena: Yeah, his classes has always felt like a pressure cooker. And these places helped us unwind.
Futaba: Exactly! But things might start getting even more tense moving forward...
Ena: Why?
Futaba: Because exams are coming up.
Futaba: The ones trying to get into art school are probably going to start practicing even harder...
Futaba: And I feel like I need to do the same.
Ena: Oh...
Ena: (Right... Futaba's already thinking about that.)
Futaba: So, Ena, where do you want to go for university?
Ena: Huh? Me?
Futaba: Yeah, because I really like your art... I feel that it'd be a huge shame if you didn't try to get accepted somewhere.
Ena: Oh, uhh...
Ena: (Art school, huh?)
Ena: (I still can't really see myself getting accepted into one.)
Ena: (I mean, I want to go. I want to keep studying art...)
Ena: (But the current me still doesn't have what it takes...)
Ena: (I wasn't able to commit to my art before. Yeah, I'm back in class now, but...)
Ena: (How am I supposed to get accepted anywhere? I know I have to get a lot better in order to...)
Futaba: Oh, Ena, I'm sorry... Were you still undecided?
Ena: Oh, umm... Yeah, kinda. Or rather, I haven't had time to think about that lately.
Ena: Anyway, let's get another dessert! This seasonal cake looks way too good.
Ena: We can split it!
Futaba: Hehe. Okay. Then, let's get it.
Futaba: Excuse me. We'd like to make an order.
Ena: *Sigh*
Ena: (She has a point... I really do need to start thinking about my future...)
Ena: (But...)
Ena: (I still don't have the skills nor the commitment...)
Ena: (I'm struggling to keep up with the others in class, and my illustrations still aren't doing N25's songs justice.)
Ena: (As much as I want to become an artist, I doubt I'll be able to at this rate.)
Ena: (So, how am I supposed to get into art school like the others...?)
???: <Ena?>
Ena: Huh...? What are you two doing here?
Rin: <We came to see how you were doing.>
Len: <Oh, um... We just wanted to see you while you drew again is all.>
Ena: Really? I doubt I was able to put on much of a show for you guys...
Rin: <That's not true...>
Rin: <We thought you were really cool.>
Rin: <And you've become so much stronger.>
Ena: What...?
Rin: <That's what we thought when we saw you drawing earlier. You had such a serious look on your face.>
Ena: I mean, I was being serious. Everyone around me was also...
Rin: <That's not what I mean. The girl I saw before looked like she was in pain whenever she drew.>
Ena: Oh...
Rin: <You drew as you struggled through that pain...>
Rin: <But things seemed different today.>
Rin: <You were facing your art head on.>
Rin: <You have the strength to face that pain now...>
Ena: Rin...
Ena: Thanks. I really appreciate you always looking out for me...
Ena: That means I need to start doing better...
Len: <What?>
Ena: Something crossed my mind just now.
Ena: I want to keep drawing... But is it really okay for me to?
Rin: <Where's that coming from?>
Ena: So... I'm better now compared to before, but I'm nowhere near the level of Futaba and the others. Plus, my illustrations still aren't doing N25's songs justice.
Ena: Which is why I'm wondering if it's really okay for me to try to go where they're going, to study art and to work towards the same goal...
Rin: <Ena...>
